HEADWORD: Kibe
<hw>Kibe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[W. <ets>cib + gwst</ets>
pain, sickness.]</ety> <def>A chap or crack in the flesh occasioned by
cold; an ulcerated chilblain.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧He galls his
<xex>kibe</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

